{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, computational complexity, a significant factor affecting the real-time performance of emotion recognition systems, remains largely unexplored in most studies.",
    "Another significant gap lies in the insufficient attention to system robustness, reliability, and context awareness.",
    "These factors are especially pivotal for systems deployed in critical applications such as healthcare, where consistent performance, context sensitivity, and resilience to external disturbances are crucial.",
    "Moreover, transparency and explainability are also inadequately addressed in existing MER studies.",
    "Understanding how these systems reach certain decisions is crucial, particularly for applications in sensitive domains."
  ]
}